  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm working tree clean, branch `work/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1`, baseline build passes. Load knowledge files. Declare RIGOR LEVEL: FULL.</step>
    <step order="1">Read spec.md FR-17, design.md §5 ("Approval queue"), and `bff-extensions.md`. Confirm `GateType.Custom` is OUT of MVP per spec.</step>
    <step order="2">Create `Gates/GateType.cs` — 5-value enum with XML doc comments explaining each gate-type's semantics + when to use it.</step>
    <step order="3">Create `Gates/GateRequest.cs` — immutable `record` carrying all 8 fields enumerated in `&lt;goal&gt;`. Use `IReadOnlyCollection&lt;string&gt;` for `AuthorizedApproverRoles`. Use `JsonElement?` for `Payload`. Default `TimeoutSeconds = 300`.</step>
    <step order="4">Create `Gates/GateOutcome.cs` — immutable `record` carrying `GateDecision` enum + 4 supporting fields. Decision enum: `Approved | Rejected | TimedOut | Pending`.</step>
    <step order="5">Create `Gates/IGateResolver.cs` — single async method `Task&lt;GateOutcome&gt; ResolveAsync(GateRequest request, CancellationToken ct)`. XML doc explains audit obligation per ADR-015 and timeout uniformity.</step>
    <step order="6">Add `AddGatesFeature()` private helper inside `AddActionEngineModule.cs` (or create if not yet existing per task 014). Register only the contract scaffold here; resolver impls register in their own tasks via `.TryAddKeyedScoped&lt;IGateResolver, ...&gt;(GateType.X, ...)` pattern (decision: keyed-DI with `GateType` as the key, so the orchestrator can resolve the right impl per Action).</step>
    <step order="7">Update `Services/Ai/PublicContracts/IActionEngineFacade.cs` (created by task 015) IF needed to expose a `RequestGateAsync(GateRequest)` method for CRUD-side consumers. If facade does not yet handle gates in MVP, skip this step and add a deferred-to-Phase-4 note in `current-task.md`.</step>
    <step order="8">Build: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` exits 0. Run any existing ActionEngine unit tests; add a minimal contract test that asserts `IGateResolver` is keyed-resolvable by `GateType` and that DI registration count stays within ADR-010 budget (≤15 non-framework).</step>
    <step order="9">Measure publish-size delta: `dotnet publish --configuration Release --runtime linux-x64 --self-contained false` before and after; record delta in `notes/measurements/030-publish-size-delta.md`. Expected &lt; 0.1 MB.</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run quality gates: `code-review` (substantive — check XML doc comments, immutability, ADR-015 audit hook semantics), `adr-check` (verify ADR-001/008/010/013/015/019/029 satisfied).</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 030 ✅. Update `current-task.md`: 030 complete; next pending = parallel Group D (031, 032, 033, 034) + 036 (parallel-safe with Group D).</step>
    <step order="11">Commit + push branch update. Document any contract decisions in `notes/decisions/030-gateresolver-contract.md` for resolver implementers (031–034) to reference.</step>
  </steps>

